cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.RO 

This paper discusses off-policy learning algorithms in the framework of Markov Decision Processes, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves optimization and control theory, which are relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper includes experiments on Garnet problems, which are related to robotics and automation, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible sub-category as well.
